@node Introduction

Introduction

Idea of program by Martin Lindhorst

If you are online in the internet and HostJunkey is running,
HostJunkey will store all names and IPs of hosts you connect to.
You can output them by pressing a hotkey. There are exists one
hotkey for output the name of the host and another for the IP.
A third hotkey is for popup a history window where you can
select the host you want to output via hotkey.
You can popup the window in every screen. The output works
like pressing the string with you keyboard. You can write
that to gadgets,shells,etc...
The system is very simular to PowerSnap.

*** IMPORTANT ***

HostJunkey has to be activated before the application you want
to store the hosts from.
HostJunkey does not free all the allocated memory on exit.
Caused by the patches it does. It`s no bug. But it`s only 32 bytes
per patch/application. Don`t quit and run HostJunkey very often,
or you memory will be much fracmented. (or use Poolmem).
The best way to use HostJunkey is to run is in the WBStartup
or before the TCP/IP stack launches. And not to remove it.
It is optional.... make your own expiriences...

PS: sorry for the bad english....I sleeped in this lessons..

@endnode

@node Requirements

Requirements

- 680x0 Processor
