@endnode

@node Usage

Usage

Patch:

1.Hotkey:

Standard Hotkey: ALT SHIFT h

Opens the history window.
On the top of the window is a cyclegadget where
to select the way of sorting the hosts.
Available is sorting by sequence,name and IP.
Under the cyclegadget is a listview with all
stored hosts. The selected host will be output
with the other two hotkeys.

2.Hotkey:

Standard Hotkey: ALT SHIFT j

Output the last, or in the history selected >hostname<.
example: www.playstation.com

3.Hotkey:

Standard Hotkey: ALT SHIFT k

Output the last, or in the history selected >hostip<.
example: 145.87.45.2


Exchange:

Active/Inactive...Enable/Disable storing of hosts
Remove............Quit HostJunkey

Prefs:

The prefs are stored in the file ENVARC:HostJunkey.prefs

The format of the file is very easy:

Line 1...Hotkey for history window
Line 2...Hotkey for output hostname
Line 3...Hotkey for output hostip

Only working in registered version:
Line 4...The value for the maximal stored hosts (1..32000)

All lines have to be ended with RETURN.

The hotkeys are standard commodity string like ALT SHIFT h.
The format is <qualifiers> <key>.

Qualifiers:

ALT,LALT,RALT...............ALT keys
COMMAND,LCOMMAND,RCOMMAND...Amiga keys
SHIFT,LSHIFT,RSHIFT.........Shift keys
CTRL........................Control key
NUMPAD......................Key on numpad

Special keys:

TAB.........................Tabulator
SPACE.......................Space
RETURN......................Return
ESC.........................Escape key
F1,F2,F3,..,F10.............Function keys
BACKSPACE...................Backspace
DEL.........................DEL key
HELP........................HELP key
NUMPAD ENTER................Enter key on numpad
CURSOR_UP...................Cursor up key
CURSOR_DOWN.................Cursor down key
CURSOR_LEFT.................Cursor left key
CURSOR_RIGHT................Cursor right key

